learning_outcomes.en:
Upon successful completion of the course students:
-	have received an overview of the development trends in Estonian folk costumes, of the influences and of the differences and similarities of the costumes as well as accessories of different regions, of the materials, design and ornamentation;
-	know and can distinguish different development periods of folk costumes;
-	know the influences of urbanization on folk costumes at the end of the 19th century;
-	have an overview of the influences of neighboring countries on Estonian folk costumes;
-	can use written resources on the basis of which are able to prepare, both in theory and in practice, folk costumes of different Estonian parishes for women, men and children.

learning_outcomes.et:
Aine edukal läbimisel üliõpilane:
- on saanud ülevaate Eesti rahvarõivaste arengusuundadest, mõjutustest, erinevate piirkondade rõivaste ja aksessuaaride  erinevustest ja sarnasustest, materjalidest, kujundusest ja ornamentidest;
- tunneb ja suudab eristada rahvariiete erinevaid arenguetappe;
- tunneb rahvariiete funktsionaalseid omadusi;
- tunneb linnastumise mõjusid rahvariietele 19. saj lõpus;
- omab ülevaadet naabermaade mõjutustest eesti rahvariietes; 
- valdab erinevate Eesti kihelkondade rahvariidekomplektide koostamise metoodikat.
